-- Argentina's dollar Par bond drops 7.6 pct in OTC market - data
-- 
-- Thu Jul 31, 2014 10:37AM EDT
-- None



BUENOS AIRES, July 31 (Reuters) - Argentina's dollar-denominated Par bond <ARPARD=RASL> slid 7.6 percent to hit a bid price of 52.00 in the first moments of trading on the over-the-counter market on Thursday after the government defaulted on its debt, Thomson Reuters data showed.

